title: Wisconsin ADRC 2020 U19
qiita_study_title: Gut microbiome alterations in Alzheimers disease _ WI 2020

experiment_design_description: gut samples from patients with and without dementia
library_construction_protocol: Fecal samples, suspended in lysis buffer/phenol:chloroform, were processed by bead beating and the genomic DNA in the recovered aqueous phase then precipitated with the addition of 0.1-volume 3_M sodium acetate and 1-volume isopropanol, incubated on ice, and centrifuged (4_C, 20_min at 18,000 x g). After rinsing with 100% ethanol and drying, the DNA pellet was dissolved in TE buffer (10_mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 1_mM EDTA) then column-purified using the NucleoSpin Gel and PCR Clean-up kit (Macherey-Nagel Inc., Bethlehem, PA). DNA concentration was measured using the Qubit BR dsDNA assay (Invitrogen, Eugene, OR). The variable region V4 amplicon of the bacterial 16S rRNA gene was amplified

After rinsing with 100% ethanol and drying, the DNA pellet was dissolved in TE buffer (10_mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 1_mM EDTA) then column-purified using the NucleoSpin Gel and PCR Clean-up kit (Macherey-Nagel Inc., Bethlehem, PA). DNA concentration was measured using the Qubit BR dsDNA assay (Invitrogen, Eugene, OR). The variable region V4 amplicon of the bacterial 16S rRNA gene was amplified

experiment_design_description: gut samples from patients with and without dementia
library_construction_protocol: Fecal samples, suspended in lysis buffer/phenol:chloroform, were processed by bead beating and the genomic DNA in the recovered aqueous phase then precipitated with the addition of 0.1-volume 3_M sodium acetate and 1-volume isopropanol, incubated on ice, and centrifuged (4_C, 20_min at 18,000 x g). After rinsing with 100% ethanol and drying, the DNA pellet was dissolved in TE buffer (10_mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 1_mM EDTA) then column-purified using the NucleoSpin Gel and PCR Clean-up kit (Macherey-Nagel Inc., Bethlehem, PA). DNA concentration was measured using the Qubit BR dsDNA assay (Invitrogen, Eugene, OR). The variable region V4 amplicon of the bacterial 16S rRNA gene was amplified

experiment_design_description: gut samples from patients with and without dementia
library_construction_protocol: Fecal samples, suspended in lysis buffer/phenol:chloroform, were processed by bead beating and the genomic DNA in the recovered aqueous phase then precipitated with the addition of 0.1-volume 3_M sodium acetate and 1-volume isopropanol, incubated on ice, and centrifuged (4_C, 20_min at 18,000 x g). After rinsing with 100% ethanol and drying, the DNA pellet was dissolved in TE buffer (10_mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 1_mM EDTA) then column-purified using the NucleoSpin Gel and PCR Clean-up kit (Macherey-Nagel Inc., Bethlehem, PA). DNA concentration was measured using the Qubit BR dsDNA assay (Invitrogen, Eugene, OR). The variable region V4 amplicon of the bacterial 16S rRNA gene was amplified

After rinsing with 100% ethanol and drying, the DNA pellet was dissolved in TE buffer (10_mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 1_mM EDTA) then column-purified using the NucleoSpin Gel and PCR Clean-up kit (Macherey-Nagel Inc., Bethlehem, PA). DNA concentration was measured using the Qubit BR dsDNA assay (Invitrogen, Eugene, OR). The variable region V4 amplicon of the bacterial 16S rRNA gene was amplified

library_construction_protocol: Fecal samples, suspended in lysis buffer/phenol:chloroform, were processed by bead beating and the genomic DNA in the recovered aqueous phase then precipitated with the addition of 0.1-volume 3_M sodium acetate and 1-volume isopropanol, incubated on ice, and centrifuged (4_C, 20_min at 18,000 x g). After rinsing with 100% ethanol and drying, the DNA pellet was dissolved in TE buffer (10_mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 1_mM EDTA) then column-purified using the NucleoSpin Gel and PCR Clean-up kit (Macherey-Nagel Inc., Bethlehem, PA). DNA concentration was measured using the Qubit BR dsDNA assay (Invitrogen, Eugene, OR). The variable region V4 amplicon of the bacterial 16S rRNA gene was amplified

library_construction_protocol: Fecal samples, suspended in lysis buffer/phenol:chloroform, were processed by bead beating and the genomic DNA in the recovered aqueous phase then precipitated with the addition of 0.1-volume 3_M sodium acetate and 1-volume isopropanol, incubated on ice, and centrifuged (4_C, 20_min at 18,000 x g). After rinsing with 100% ethanol and drying, the DNA pellet was dissolved in TE buffer (10_mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 1_mM EDTA) then column-purified using the NucleoSpin Gel and PCR Clean-up kit (Macherey-Nagel Inc., Bethlehem, PA). DNA concentration was measured using the Qubit BR dsDNA assay (Invitrogen, Eugene, OR). The variable region V4 amplicon of the bacterial 16S rRNA gene was amplified

library_construction_protocol: Fecal samples, suspended in lysis buffer/phenol:chloroform, were processed by bead beating and the genomic DNA in the recovered aqueous phase then precipitated with the addition of 0.1-volume 3_M sodium acetate and 1-volume isopropanol, incubated on ice, and centrifuged (4_C, 20_min at 18,000 x g). After rinsing with 100% ethanol and drying, the DNA pellet was dissolved in TE buffer (10_mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 1_mM EDTA) then column-purified using the NucleoSpin Gel and PCR Clean-up kit (Macherey-Nagel Inc., Bethlehem, PA). DNA concentration was measured using the Qubit BR dsDNA assay (Invitrogen, Eugene, OR). The variable region V4 amplicon of the bacterial 16S rRNA gene was amplified

library_construction_protocol: Fecal samples, suspended in lysis buffer/phenol:chloroform, were processed by bead beating and the genomic DNA in the recovered aqueous phase then precipitated with the addition of 0.1-volume 3_M sodium acetate and 1-volume isopropanol, incubated on ice, and centrifuged (4_C, 20_min at 18,000 x g). After rinsing with 100% ethanol and drying, the DNA pellet was dissolved in TE buffer (10_mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 1_mM EDTA) then column-purified using the NucleoSpin Gel and PCR Clean-up kit (Macherey-Nagel Inc., Bethlehem, PA). DNA concentration was measured using the Qubit BR dsDNA assay (Invitrogen, Eugene, OR). The variable region V4 amplicon of the bacterial 16S rRNA gene was amplified
